 ### The  :/  vs  :=  Operator in  dist

  Interviewer question: "What is the difference between  :=  and  :/  in a distribution?"
  Answer:

  •  :=  assigns the weight to EVERY individual item in a range.
  •  :/  DIVIDES the weight equally across the items in a range.

  Example:
  If we have a range from 1 to 4:  [1:4]  (which is four numbers: 1, 2, 3, 4).

  •  [1:4] := 40  -> 1 gets 40, 2 gets 40, 3 gets 40, 4 gets 40. (Total weight = 160).
  •  [1:4] :/ 40  -> The 40 is divided by four. So 1 gets 10, 2 gets 10, 3 gets 10, 4 gets 10. (Total weight = 40).
